<Author>STR17
<Content>Dissapointed... I stayed at this hotel this month for 8 days, part of my 17 days trip to London, Paris, and Amsterdam. In short, this hotel barely meets my expectation..it is probably because my expecation was too high, the fact that hotel is 4-star rated, and how great the reviews I found in this forum. In fact, the reviews here that led me to choose this hotel. But, I am totally dissapointed.To be fair, let's start with the good ones:* Location is superb.. a short walk to metro station, 10-20minutes walk to many major destinations and shopping center.* What's more, a supermarket which opens till 10pm is right in front of the hotel. A Chinese/Viet restaurant is just next door, this is really great as I am very traditional Asian in terms of food.* Bathroom is nice, clean, tidy, and modern look.* One of the staff, the lady, is very friendly and helpful ( I met 5 different staffs during my stay)What dissapoints me? Bed is #1 problem, but it is a long list.* Room size is very small, i had managed my expectation before, that's why I booked Junior Suite room not standard or superior...this junior suite turned out just to be a small tiny room. They must be kidding calling this suite room of a 4-star hotel. I would rather call this a bigger small room, because I believe standard and superior room would be even much smaller.* No fridge, no a kind of tea facilities, etc. We had to put my baby's medicine in their refrigator in the bar at ground floor, while we stayed in sixth floor. But, i would agree with them that the room is just too small to put a fridge/minibar.* A small TV in the corner is placed on top of weird and small metal platform. Everytime i opened the window too wide it always hit the TV since it is located in the small corner next to the window* And the bed; the main reason you stay in a hotel is too sleep not to have a good breakfast or good wine. We were promised a king size bed, but it is actually two single beds that are put together! Worse, mattress is very soft. As a result, tt keep drifted away each other, and this really disturbed me since my baby slept in the middle; The staff said that it is impossible to get king size mattress, that's it. Baby cot? we dont need it, also the fact that the room is very small for a baby cot.* it is said they have some antique furniture in the room, some might like it, but I dont, i prefer the functionality. The drawer of this antiques cant be used easily, for instance. But, the problem is one or two antique furniture doesnt really match with the overall room design. Bathroom is modern look, bed frame is a simple basic modern, tv cabinet is tiny weird metal platform, etc. and suddenly you have two antique stuff, with worn out carpet. What's more, the exterior in very narrow hallway is in a bit dark pink, bringing contemporer nuance..so, is it classic, antique, modern, contemporer, or what? * The hotel staff in an email that my room would face courtyard, but having stayed there 8 days, i struggled to find the courtyard, what I can see from 6th flloor is just the roof from the adjacent buildings. There might be tiny small narrow courtyard downthere, but you have to take extra effort to look down.* I did not make a lot of contact with the staffss, but nothing special with staff services, except for the lady that I mentioned above. Another guy also looks very nice, but, generally they are just average if not below average. The staff could not help me with basic questions like internet cafe or southeast asian/thailand/indonesian restaurant in the neighboorhood. He just gave me the clipping of restaurant brochures/business cards, to be honest lonely planet or insight guide provide much more exhaustive list. * FYI, they just have one staff at one time, so dont expect too much. Whenever we borrowed something like adapter or spoons we generally have to come down, even when my wife deliberately asked whether she had to come down to lobby or it could be delivered to our room, given she was busy with the baby, the staf said we had to come down. In one ocassion, another staff really offered to deliver it to my room.* No one would approach you to although you struggle opening the door with luggages and baby strollers. During the check out the staff didnt ask me any single question about my experience staying there. He didnt ask me either where we would go, if he could help something, since we were with baby and a lot of luggage, say.. offering calling a taxi, etc. Nothing, he just showed me the invoice (which is hand written). That's all. He is not rude, anyway, but he just didnt talk much. I felt just like buying burger in fastfood restaurant, at best, although I stayed in this hotel for an 8 day long.In a nuthshell, this might be not bad hotel, esp. due to location, but I just dont understand how come this hotel rated 4 star and got so many favorable review here. it should be 2 or 3 star hotel at best, in my opinion.If i had known about the hotel overall quality, i would have gone to Hilton Arc de Triomph which then offered deals about only 10% higher rate than this Le Lavoisier hotel. In fact, I discussed at length with my wife between this hotel and Hilton Arc, before we decide opting this hotel, because it is slightly cheaper, closer to metro station, and more importantly we got Junior Suite room! At times, you will make wrong decision, though. 
