<Author>robstef
<Content>Le Lavoisier, classy,cool and chic., Stayed at Le Lavoisier with my wife and 9 year old daughter for two nights in July 2006, This is a quite delightful hotel and we will definitely return. Price is reasonable for Paris.The hotel is spotlessly clean and the room we had (on 3rd floor) was certainly not huge but took a double bed and an extra bed for my daughter easily with still some space to move around. Having said this my son and his wife were staying in the hotel at the same time (we had, unknowingly, booked into the hotel at the same time - synchronicity or what?) and his room, allegedly a suite with a jacuzzi bath did seem a little cramped and dingy. The only natural light was from a little ante-room, the window of which looked straight out onto a wall of the next building. Nonetheless, it was, as our room was, nicely furnished. The bathrooms were excellent, all white marble and tiles, and again, very clean. This hotel was a Town House and it still manages to retain some of the feel of that, yet at the same time with a modern touch. It has class. Someone has taken some care over the decor and furnishings.While we were there, it was a heat wave. Thank goodness then for the very efficient air conditioning in the rooms. After a day dashing round the tourist sites it was like coming back to an oasis. So cool!The Hotel is well situated - it really is in a quiet side street. There is no traffic noise. The metro is just round the corner as is a very impressive supermarket. One or two good restaurants to be found in the area too. Last but not least, the staff. The two young women who were on duty at the reception during our time there could not have been more helpful, charming, knowledgeable and just plain delightful. As a bonus, they were also attractive, sexy and chic (hope they don't mind me saying so).It would be wrong not to mention the breakfast ( which was more than adequate) and the absolutely charming guy who was serving. We had a terrific stay at this hotel and much of this was down to the efficiency and courtesy of the staff.In terms of hotels in this class, in this price bracket, Le Lavoisier must be hard to beat. I really hope they manage to sustain this level of service (at least until I get to stay there again). 
