<Content>A 2 star hotel We stayed at this hotel recently and found it rather disappointing. The staff are friendly and helpful, but no more than what we've encountered elsewhere. The room was clean but average. No fridge, no safe or shower curtain and only a tiny and tatty looking television. The kingsize bed was actually two beds pushed together. The matresses were very uncomfortable.Nothing about the place delighted us, or exceeded our expectations.We had requested a non-smoking room on a high floor. We were allocated a smoking room on the second floor. We were left with the choice of staying there or moving to another, but smaller, smoking room. Incidentally, we were told that all rooms have ashtrays as standard. Reception informed us that the housekeeper would spray the room with deodoriser. It wasn't the response we wanted to hear.There was no hot water for two of the three days. This was explained as something to do with public works in the city. We have never encountered this before in a 4 star hotel. The breakfast room is in the basement. No natural light, and the ambience is on the drab side. It's possibly the saddest room we've ever ate in.On the plus side, the hotel is in a reasonable neighbourhood and the metro is nearby. Paris is a great place, and we had a wonderful time in the city. Based on the reviews, though, Le Lavoisier was a disappointment. Given the chance, we would probably book Hotel Sezz or Hotel Esprit Saint Germain. 
