<Content>Good value, good service Stayed for 3 nights last week  had no real problems at all.I originally booked a slightly larger room than the standard (room 16 I think)  it was spacious for a Parisian hotel room, but the only window looked out onto a wall. This we then changed with no problems to a smaller room with a window overlooking the street (room 12) which we were very happy with.The toilet was very small, fully tiled, clean  separate to the bathroom which was the same.All the staff spoke very good English, were relaxed polite  very helpful with any requests.Although the hotel classes itself as a 4 star, I don`t think it would strictly meet that criteria (in my humble opinion) for a few minor reasons - no tea/ coffee making facilities, room safe, or mini bar in the standard room we stayed in.The hotel was very smart looking from both outside  inside decor  the rooms also,  very clean too.The location was one of the best I`ve stated at in Paris - 200 yards from St. Augustin church  10 mins walk from Place de Madeleine  400 yards to Augustin metro stop.Hope this doesn`t seem like a negative post as it`s not intended to be. I would definately return to this hotel again  I have already recommended it to friends who I think are going to go there in the spring. 
